# Coding Standards: Component Architecture & Control Flow

## 1. Functional Components

- Use functional components exclusively. Do not use class-based components.
- Define components using either:
  - Standard function declarations (for example, `export default function ComponentName() { ... }`), or
  - Arrow functions,
  based on the project's existing style consistency.

## 2. Guard Clauses & Early Returns

- Prioritize early returns (guard clauses) at the top of functions/components to handle:
  - Loading states
  - Errors
  - Null/undefined checks
  - Edge cases
- Keep the primary execution path at the outermost indentation level.
- Do not wrap the main return path in `if/else` blocks when guard clauses can flatten the logic.
- Avoid deep nesting for primary rendering logic.

## 3. Example

### Incorrect (Deep Nesting / Main path inside conditional)

```tsx
function UserProfile({ user, isLoading }) {
  if (!isLoading) {
    if (user) {
      return (
        <div>
          <h1>{user.name}</h1>
          <p>{user.email}</p>
        </div>
      );
    } else {
      return <div>User not found</div>;
    }
  } else {
    return <div>Loading...</div>;
  }
}
```

### Correct (Early Returns / Guard Clauses)

```tsx
function UserProfile({ user, isLoading }) {
  // Guard clause 1: Loading state
  if (isLoading) return <div>Loading...</div>;

  // Guard clause 2: Error/Null state
  if (!user) return <div>User not found</div>;

  // Primary execution path is flat
  return (
    <div>
      <h1>{user.name}</h1>
      <p>{user.email}</p>
    </div>
  );
}
```
